The paper deals with game theory and decision making in dynamic environments, which are topics that are commonly studied in the subfield of computational game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses reinforcement learning algorithms, which fall under the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper addresses Markov Decision Processes (MDPs) and stochastic games, which are topics that are commonly studied in the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with control and optimization, which are topics that are commonly studied in the subfield of control systems (cs.SY) and mathematical optimization (cs.MA).
